Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven
to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed), separating whites from greens. Peel and
mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}. Dice @sweet potatoes{1} into ½-inch pieces. Trim and
quarter @cremini mushrooms{8%ounce}(trimmed) (skip if your mushrooms are pre-sliced!).
Core, deseed, and dice @bell pepper{1}(core and deseeded) into ½-inch pieces.

== Ginger Rice ==

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} in a small #pot{} over medium-high heat. Add scallion
whites and 1 tablespoon ginger; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, @water{1 1/4%cups}, and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to
a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender,
~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Roasted Veggies ==

Meanwhile, in a medium #bowl{}, toss sweet potato and mushrooms with a drizzle of
@cooking oil{1%teaspoon}, half the hoisin sauce (you'll use the rest later),
@salt{}, and @pepper{}. Spread out on one side of a #baking sheet{}.

Toss bell pepper on empty side with a drizzle of oil, salt, and pepper.

(For 4 servings, use 2 sheets; roast sweet potatoes and mushrooms on top rack and
bell peppers on middle rack.)

Roast on top rack until veggies are just tender, about ~{15%minutes} (they'll finish
cooking in Step 5).

== Chili Soy Mayo ==

While veggies roast, in a small bowl, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon},
@sour cream{1.5%tablespoon}, @soy sauce{2%tablespoon}, and as much
@sweet Thai chili sauce{1%ounce} as you like.

> Start with half the chili sauce, then taste and add more from there if you like
> things spicy.

== Finish Veggies ==

Once veggies have roasted 15 minutes, remove baking sheet from oven. (For 4
servings, remove sheet with sweet potatoes and mushrooms; leave bell peppers
roasting.) Using a #spatula{}, carefully toss sweet potato and mushrooms with
remaining @hoisin sauce{2%tablespoon} and half the @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon}
(save the rest for serving).

Return to oven until veggies are tender and glaze is tacky, ~{5-8%minutes} more.

== Salmon ==

Pat @salmon{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large, preferably nonstick, pan over
medium-high heat. Add salmon (skin sides down). Cook salmon until skin is crisp,
~{5-7%minutes}, then flip and cook until cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes} more.
Transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest.

> Salmon is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

== Assembly ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{} and season with salt; divide between #bowls{}.

Arrange sweet potato and mushrooms and bell pepper over rice in separate sections.
Drizzle everything with as much chili soy mayo as you like. Top with scallion greens
and remaining sesame seeds. Serve.

Slice salmon crosswise. Serve salmon atop bowls.